<subSubSection id="C341656890180E6DFD2EFC11FB17FB34" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE436E390180E6DFD2EFC11FB17FB34" blockId="1.[714,1248,556,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">DIAGNOSIS. — Cephalic lobe triangular. Pereon segments 5-7 and pleon segments 1-3 smooth. Urosomite 1 with well developed dorsal tooth. Gnathopod 1, carpus slightly longer than propodus; palm transverse. Gnathopod 2, carpus subequal in length to propodus; propodus robust; palm oblique. Coxa 4 shallowly excavate posteriorly. Basis of pereopod 7 narrowing on postero-distal margin. Outer ramus of uropod 3 with proximal article a little longer than twice the length of distal article. Telson cleft to about 5/6 of its length.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C341656890180E6FFD2EFB43FD7AFC44" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="190" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE436E390180E6DFD2EFB43FC8DFA83" blockId="1.[714,1248,1258,1669]" box="[714,859,1258,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE436E390180E6FFD2EFAA2FD7AFC44" blockId="1.[714,1248,1258,1669]" lastBlockId="3.[151,684,170,965]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="190" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Lateral cephalic lobe triangular; eyes absent (
<figureCitation id="13602A6690180E6DFD36FA82FCFEFAC4" box="[722,808,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[176,1214,211,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[194,1228,201,1570]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Valettiopsis macrodactyla Chevreux, 1909, 19.8 mm (MNRJ 15696); A, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2, above the length of antenna 1; B, callynophores of antenna 1 and flagellum accessory; C, pleon and urosome; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, C, 1.0 mm; B, E, 0.3 mm; D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757305/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Antenna 1, peduncle robust; flagellum with 35+ articles, first article conjoint (
<figureCitation id="13602A6690180E6DFB86FAE2FB07FAE5" box="[1122,1233,1354,1381]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[176,1214,211,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[194,1228,201,1570]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Valettiopsis macrodactyla Chevreux, 1909, 19.8 mm (MNRJ 15696); A, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2, above the length of antenna 1; B, callynophores of antenna 1 and flagellum accessory; C, pleon and urosome; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, C, 1.0 mm; B, E, 0.3 mm; D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757305/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Fig. 1A, B</figureCitation>
); accessory flagellum 10-articulate. Antenna 2 longer than antenna 1, flagellum with 46 articles. Mandible with incisor dentate; molar strongly triturative; palp 3-articulate, article 2 the longest with setae on inner margin. Lower lip, inner lobe absent; outer lobe marginally setose; mandibular lobe blunt and well developed. Maxilla 1, inner plate with a row of plumose setae on inner margin; outer plate with 11 denticulate spines distally; palp robust, 2-articulate. Maxilla 2, inner and outer plates densely setose; inner plate with a row of facial setae. Inner plate of maxilliped with 3 short apical spines. Coxa 1 subtriangular and shorter than the others; coxae 2-4 rectangular; coxa 4 weakly excavate posteriorly. Gnathopod 1, carpus slightly longer than propodus; carpus and propodus anterior margin sparsely setose, posterior margin densely setose; palm transverse; dactylus fitting palm. Gnathopod 2, carpus and propodus subequal in length; propodus robust, setose and distinctly wider than carpus; palm oblique; dactylus slightly shorter than palm. Basis of pereopod 5 oval. Pereopods 6-7, basis tapering distally, lacking postero-distal lobe, posterior margin weakly serrate. Epimera 2-3 acutely produced. Urosomite 1 with a well developed dorsal tooth (
<figureCitation id="13602A66901A0E6FFDA7FD02FD4AFD44" box="[579,668,683,709]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[176,1214,211,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[194,1228,201,1570]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Valettiopsis macrodactyla Chevreux, 1909, 19.8 mm (MNRJ 15696); A, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2, above the length of antenna 1; B, callynophores of antenna 1 and flagellum accessory; C, pleon and urosome; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, C, 1.0 mm; B, E, 0.3 mm; D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Uropod 1, peduncle with a strong disto-lateral spine; rami subequal in length, spinose. Uropod 2 with outer ramus shorter than inner ramus. Outer ramus of uropod 3 slightly longer than inner ramus and about 1.7 times the length of peduncle, proximal article a little longer than twice the length of distal article (
<figureCitation id="13602A66901A0E6FFEC8FC22FE53FC24" box="[300,389,907,933]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[176,1214,211,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[194,1228,201,1570]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Valettiopsis macrodactyla Chevreux, 1909, 19.8 mm (MNRJ 15696); A, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2, above the length of antenna 1; B, callynophores of antenna 1 and flagellum accessory; C, pleon and urosome; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, C, 1.0 mm; B, E, 0.3 mm; D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Telson deeply cleft, each lobe with a distal notch and 2 apical spines (
<figureCitation id="13602A66901A0E6FFDABFC02FD48FC44" box="[591,670,939,965]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[176,1214,211,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[194,1228,201,1570]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Valettiopsis macrodactyla Chevreux, 1909, 19.8 mm (MNRJ 15696); A, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2, above the length of antenna 1; B, callynophores of antenna 1 and flagellum accessory; C, pleon and urosome; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, C, 1.0 mm; B, E, 0.3 mm; D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
