<subSubSection id="C3416568901A0E6FFF73FC43FD83FA44" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE436E3901A0E6FFF73FC43FF2DFB83" blockId="3.[151,684,1002,1477]" box="[151,251,1002,1028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE436E3901A0E6FFF73FBA2FD83FA44" blockId="3.[151,684,1002,1477]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA4B12901A0E6FFF73FBA2FE07FBA4" author="LINCOLN R. J. &amp; THURSTON M. H." box="[151,465,1035,1061]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" pagination="85 - 101" refId="ref3735" refString="LINCOLN R. J. &amp; THURSTON M. H. 1983. - Valettietta, a new genus of deep-sea amphipod (Gammaridea: Lysianassidae) with descriptions of two new species from the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 44: 85 - 101." type="journal article" year="1983">Lincoln &amp; Thurston (1983)</bibRefCitation>
provided an extensive redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D60901A0E6FFE90FB83FDCDFBC4" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1909" box="[372,539,1066,1093]" class="Malacostraca" family="Valettiopsidae" genus="Valettiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrodactyla">
<emphasis id="B92FEAF1901A0E6FFE90FB83FDCDFBC4" box="[372,539,1066,1093]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">V. macrodactyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so only a few diagnostic features of this taxon have been figured here. Our material is in close agreement with the descriptions of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA4B12901A0E6FFE43FB22FD8BFB24" author="CHEVREUX E." box="[423,605,1163,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref3575" refString="CHEVREUX E. 1909. - Diagnoses d'amphipodes nouveaux provenant des campagnes de la Princesse- Alice dans l'Atlantique Nord. Bulletin de l'Institut oceanographique 150: 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1909">Chevreux (1909</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA4B12901A0E6FFD8EFB22FD75FB24" author="CHEVREUX E." box="[618,675,1163,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 214" refId="ref3605" refString="CHEVREUX E. 1935. - Amphipodes provenant des campagnes du Prince Albert Ier de Monaco. Resultats des Campagnes scientifiques accomplies par le Prince Albert Ier 90: 1 - 214." type="journal article" year="1935">1935</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA4B12901A0E6FFF2EFB02FDD8FB44" author="LINCOLN R. J. &amp; THURSTON M. H." box="[202,526,1195,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" pagination="85 - 101" refId="ref3735" refString="LINCOLN R. J. &amp; THURSTON M. H. 1983. - Valettietta, a new genus of deep-sea amphipod (Gammaridea: Lysianassidae) with descriptions of two new species from the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 44: 85 - 101." type="journal article" year="1983">Lincoln &amp; Thurston (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. The callynophore is the fused proximal articles of the primary flagellum of antenna 1, which bear transverse rows of aesthetascs, present also in females, and herein illustrated (
<figureCitation id="13602A66901A0E6FFE96FA82FE1BFAC4" box="[370,461,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1609,1626]" captionTargetBox="[176,1214,211,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[194,1228,201,1570]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Valettiopsis macrodactyla Chevreux, 1909, 19.8 mm (MNRJ 15696); A, head with peduncles of antennae 1-2, above the length of antenna 1; B, callynophores of antenna 1 and flagellum accessory; C, pleon and urosome; D, uropod 3; E, telson. Scale bars: A, C, 1.0 mm; B, E, 0.3 mm; D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). The body length varies, reaching 
<quantity id="4CA39B06901A0E6FFEB0FAE2FE4FFAE5" box="[340,409,1354,1381]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
(female) in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA4B12901A0E6FFDC8FAE2FF0CFA04" author="CHEVREUX E." pageId="3" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref3575" refString="CHEVREUX E. 1909. - Diagnoses d'amphipodes nouveaux provenant des campagnes de la Princesse- Alice dans l'Atlantique Nord. Bulletin de l'Institut oceanographique 150: 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1909">Chevreux’s (1909</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA4B12901A0E6FFF02FAC2FEC9FA04" author="CHEVREUX E." box="[230,287,1387,1413]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 214" refId="ref3605" refString="CHEVREUX E. 1935. - Amphipodes provenant des campagnes du Prince Albert Ier de Monaco. Resultats des Campagnes scientifiques accomplies par le Prince Albert Ier 90: 1 - 214." type="journal article" year="1935">1935</bibRefCitation>
) material, 
<quantity id="4CA39B06901A0E6FFE72FAC2FE33FA05" box="[406,485,1386,1413]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
(male) in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA4B12901A0E6FFDBCFAC2FE5CFA24" author="LINCOLN R. J. &amp; THURSTON M. H." pageId="3" pageNumber="190" pagination="85 - 101" refId="ref3735" refString="LINCOLN R. J. &amp; THURSTON M. H. 1983. - Valettietta, a new genus of deep-sea amphipod (Gammaridea: Lysianassidae) with descriptions of two new species from the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 44: 85 - 101." type="journal article" year="1983">Lincoln &amp; Thurston’s (1983)</bibRefCitation>
specimen, and 19.8 mm (female) in the material herein examined.
</paragraph>
